---
description: Cursor Cloud Agent rules for issue-scoped branches, PR evidence, and reviewer handoff.
globs: "agent-harness/cursor/**, examples/card-krueger/**, docs/**, materials/**"
alwaysApply: false
---

- Every cloud task needs one GitHub issue, one branch, allowed files, out-of-scope
  boundaries, acceptance criteria, and a verification plan.
- The branch name must appear in the prompt and PR body.
- The PR body must include changed files, verification evidence, reviewer role
  used, and remaining risks.
- Do not broaden a cloud task to adjacent workshop material; open a follow-up
  issue instead.
- Cloud subagents use team MCP configuration from Cursor Cloud Agent settings,
  not local `.cursor/mcp.json`. Do not assume local API keys are available.
- Do not merge a cloud-agent PR without human review, even if a verifier returns
  GREEN.
